  "text": "Symplectic methods have shown to be very effective in long time integration of Hamiltonian systems (see [CITATION_1] ). Many of them are implicit and necessitate the solution of systems of equations. If the differential equation system is large and sparse, a natural approach is to use Krylov subspace techniques to approximate solution of the algebraic equations.",
